            "source": "Benzinga",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "President Trump announced new tariffs as a way to rectify trade imbalances, introducing a reciprocal tariff rate of 50% based on what the US's trading partners charge, factoring in non-tariff barriers. The exceeding duty levels, up to mid-30% with key partners, led to a sell-off in after-hours trading. China, with tariffs up to 67%, will face 37% US duties, the EU with a 39% rate will see 20%, and Japan with 46% barriers will have a 24% duty. These measures aim to address trade disparities but have shaken investors. (Word count: 92)",
