            "is_major": false,
            "source": "Cointelegraph",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "Ether (ETH) has seen a 6.4% increase in price, but struggles to reach $2,000 due in part to the deflating memecoin market. Year-to-date, Ether is down by 44% with little bullish sentiment among traders. Premium on Ether futures is below the neutral 5% threshold, showing lack of confidence. The ETH options market indicates risk-aversion sentiment. Despite the decline in Ethereum DApps revenue, the network's adoption remains strong. Ethereum holds a high amount of stablecoins and TVL, suggesting potential for adoption. Despite challenges, the Ethereum network continues to expand. Retail traders have neutral sentiment towards Ether due to ETFs. The funding rate has been neutral since March 31. Derivatives data and sentiment indicate caution among traders and investors.",
