        {
            "beta_headline": null,
            "category": "commodities",
            "date": "2025-04-02",
            "headline": "D2L Inc. reports strong Q4 results with $53.3 million revenue, 12% YoY increase. Full-year revenue reached $205.3 million, 13% growth. Subscription and support revenue jump to $46.8 million in Q4, 11% growth YoY. Cash flow from operating activities rose to $27.9 million in Fiscal 2025, an increase of $12.2 million YoY. Adjusted EBITDA at $9.4 million in Q4. CEO expresses satisfaction with company's performance; anticipates continued growth and profitability for Fiscal 2026. Medium-term outlook expects 10-15% revenue growth and 18-20% Adjusted EBITDA margin by Fiscal 2028.",
            "id": "d141e951-e55f-4252-8c85-254885b05f4f",
            "is_major": false,
            "source": "Benzinga",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "D2L Inc., a global learning technology company, reported strong financial results for Q4 Fiscal 2025 and full year with total revenue increasing by 12% to US$53.3 million in Q4 and 13% to US$205.3 million for the full year. Q4 subscription and support revenue grew 11% to US$46.8 million, and full-year revenue in this segment increased by 11% to US$180.6 million. Constant Currency Annual Recurring Revenue reached US$205.3 million at year-end, up by 9%. Cash flow from operating activities in Fiscal 2025 was US$27.9 million, a significant increase. The Q4 Adjusted EBITDA was US$9.4 million, a notable increase from the prior year. D2L's customer base grew to over 1,430, and the company received various accolades for its learning platform. The company provided financial guidance for Fiscal 2026, predicting subscription and support revenue in the range of $194 million to $196 million, total revenue in the range of $219 million to $221 million, and Adjusted EBITDA in the range of $32 million to $34 million. This outlook reflects a balance between growth and profitability, highlighting continued investment for growth while scaling towards increased profitability.",
            "tickers": [
                "NDXP",
                "DTOL"
            ],
            "time": "21:36:04",
            "timestamp": "2025-04-02T21:36:04Z",
            "url": "https://www.benzinga.com/pressreleases/25/04/n44617678/d2l-inc-announces-fourth-quarter-and-fiscal-2025-financial-results"
        },
